title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1993-09-22
lineage: DAT Master > TASCAM DA-20 (SPDIF out) > LynxTWO-B Audio Reference Interface (SPDIF in) > Wavelab 6.0
description:
Set 1

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Minglewood Blues, Ramble On Rose, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song

Set 2

Easy Answers, Lazy River Road, Estimated Prophet-> Dark Star-> Drums-> Space-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light*, E: I Fought The Law*

David Murray on sax during Birdsong and entire second set, * w/ James Cotton on harmonica

reviews.review_text: Average 1st set is where it's at, but still a very average show.  Highlights: Slipknot!, Lazy River Road

David Murray > Branford I know this might ruffle some feathers... and I do like Branford... but I just think Murray fits in the band way better. He has a knack for when to contribute and when to step back, which helps with a band as busy as the Dead. But more than that he seems to connect on a spiritual/psychedelic level. The "Estimated" jam here is not to be missed. Overall a great show from this era, and this is a good matrix.
